revision.text:
'''Backcoating''' is the [[lamination]] of two sheets of paper back to back to create a superior paper for folding [[origami]] models. <ref Name="Robinson">{{cite book |title= The Encyclopedia Of Origami: The Complete, Fully Illustrated Guide to the Folded Paper Arts |last= Robinson |first= Nick |authorlink= Nick Robinson (paperfolder) |coauthors= |year= 2004 |publisher= Running Press |location= |isbn= 0-7624-1895-8 |page= 158 |pages= |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=iZva52ypoegC&pg=RA1-PA156&dq=backcoating+origami&client=firefox-a#v=onepage&q=backcoating%20origami&f=false}}</ref>
